The New York City
------------------------
The New York City Department of Health West Nile Virus Information
West Nile Virus Update; 25 Birds, 8 Mosquito Pools, and 1 Rabbit Test
Positive for West Nile Virus (22 Sep 2000) [edited
<http://www.ci.nyc.ny.us/html/doh/html/wnv/wnvhome.html>

New York City Health Commissioner Neal L. Cohen, M.D., announced today that
evidence of West Nile virus (WNV) has been confirmed by the New York State
Department of Health in 25 birds, 8 mosquito pools, and one [domestic
rabbit in New York City. Weather permitting, ground spraying is scheduled
for Central Park on Saturday morning [midnight  0500 hrs; & areas of
Queens & Brooklyn, weather permitting. Temperatures of 60F or lower may
necessitate postponement of spraying activities. [And restrict mosquito
activity.  Mod.JW
Dr. Cohen said, "Despite today's announcement of the presence of virus in 34
additional specimens, we will only need to initiate new control activities
in 4 areas because our surveillance activities previously gave us sufficient
warning to have targeted those remaining areas in a timely manner."
Bird, Mammal & Mosquito Findings
The positive WNV findings announced today include:
In Queens, 4 birds (starling, house sparrow & 2 crows) collected between 2
Aug & 11 Sep 2000.
In Brooklyn, 9 birds, (robin, 8 crows) collected between 25 Aug & 9 Sep 2000.
In Manhattan, 4 crows: one from Harlem collected 8 Sep 2000, one from
Central Park collected 8 Sep 2000, & 2 from the Upper West Side collected 10
Sep 2000, and one mosquito pool collected in Central Park on 9 Sep 2000.
In the Bronx, one sparrow, collected in Port Morris 31 Jul 2000.
On Staten Island, 7 birds (6 crows & a grackle) collected between 7 & 12 Sep
2000, 5 mosquito pools one collected from 6-12 Sep 2000, & one [domestic
rabbit collected on 28 Aug 2000.
