Pennsylvania
----------------
Pennsylvania's West Nile Virus Surveillance Program
http://www.westnile.state.pa.us/StateSummary/
WEEKLY REPORT - SEPTEMBER 11, 2000 [edited

This report summarizes Pennsylvania's Mosquito Surveillance Program from 1-7
Sep 2000.
To date West Nile virus (WNV) has not been found in Pennsylvania.
Pennsylvania's Mosquito Surveillance Program began on April 3. Currently, 37
counties have active surveillance programs, with 3660 surveillance sites. 47
counties are currently in routine surveillance, and 20 counties are
currently in enhanced surveillance.
Mosquito Sampling To Date
Samples Collected 6726
Samples Contain Mosquitoes
Appropriate for Testing 842
Negative results for WNV 375
Samples with Results Pending 467

Bird Sampling To Date
Bird Samples Collected 372
Birds Tested for WNV 349
Negative results for WNV 137
Birds with Results Pending 212
[It is quite striking that although counties all over Pennsylvania have
submitted bird samples for testing, there have so far (as of 7 Sep 2000, the
latest available information) been no positives, considering that all the NY
state counties bordering on Pennsylvania have produced positives  see map
<http://nationalatlas.gov/virusmap/w36/wnavi36c.gif>
The same applies to Vermont & New Hampshire (the latter bordering on
positive counties in Massachusetts). The enzootic (outbreak in birds) seems
to be spreading quite slowly  apart from the jump to southern Maryland. 
Mod.JW
